12
00:01:16,070 --> 00:01:16,950
Give it back!

13
00:01:16,970 --> 00:01:17,730
No.

14
00:01:17,950 --> 00:01:19,280
Are you a rebellious teen?

15
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:20,120
Don't you care about your knee at all?

16
00:01:20,120 --> 00:01:21,230
Can you leave me alone?

17
00:01:21,230 --> 00:01:22,070
No!

18
00:01:22,510 --> 00:01:23,710
If you're afraid others will find out,

19
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:25,350
just say you're accompanying me.

20
00:01:25,350 --> 00:01:25,840
I'm not going.

21
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:26,900
Give me back my bag.

22
00:01:26,930 --> 00:01:27,490
No.

23
00:01:28,230 --> 00:01:28,840
I won't.

24
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:32,220
Come and take it!

25
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:35,610
[Close to You]

26
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:38,090
[EP. 15: I Saw the Daytime Shooting Star]

27
00:02:38,290 --> 00:02:39,750
[Department of Sports Medicine;
Department of Rehabilitation Medicine]

28
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:42,320
Your condition is still quite serious.

29
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,610
Do you feel it swelling?

30
00:02:49,079 --> 00:02:52,280
If it feels swollen, that means
the treatment is working.

31
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,520
Remember:

32
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:58,329
